{"id":34751,"title":"Growth and development. Bone dysplasia--a frequent cause of short stature in children.","abstract":"In children presenting with short stature, physicians often limit themselves to descriptive diagnoses such as idiopathic short stature or small for gestational age. Flechtner and colleagues now report a high frequency of bone dysplasias in these children, raising questions about the process of diagnosing short stature.","date":"2014-05-21","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24709662","annotations":[{"name":"Idiopathic","weight":0.381855,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Idiopathic"},{"name":"Gestational age","weight":0.30685,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gestational_age"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.259055,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Bone","weight":0.258455,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bone"},{"name":"Short stature","weight":0.222846,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Short_stature"},{"name":"Physician","weight":0.0805305,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physician"},{"name":"Birth mass","weight":0.0400013,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Birth_mass"},{"name":"Frequency","weight":0.0397094,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frequency"},{"name":"Idiopathic short stature","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Idiopathic_short_stature"},{"name":"High frequency","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/High_frequency"},{"name":"Developmental biology","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Developmental_biology"},{"name":"Linguistic description","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linguistic_description"},{"name":"Short film","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http:/